docs.abstract: In an interview, Stephen Moore maintained his view that rate increases were wrong, but said he regretted his harsh criticism of Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome H. Powell over them.
docs.snippet: In an interview, Stephen Moore maintained his view that rate increases were wrong, but said he regretted his harsh criticism of Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome H. Powell over them.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Stephen Moore said he would not be a “sycophant” for President Trump if nominated and confirmed for a seat on the Federal Reserve. And he is sorry he called for the Fed chairman to step down after the central bank raised interest rates.

headline.main: He’s No ‘Sycophant’ for Trump, Expected Fed Nominee Says
headline.print_headline: Expected Nominee for Fed Seat Says He’s Not ‘a Sycophant for Trump’

byline.original: By Jim Tankersley and Neil Irwin

docs.abstract: Edward Stack became a prominent voice for gun safety after the deadly mass shooting in Parkland, Fla., last year. That may be taking a toll on his business.
docs.snippet: Edward Stack became a prominent voice for gun safety after the deadly mass shooting in Parkland, Fla., last year. That may be taking a toll on his business.
docs.lead_paragraph: Dick’s Sporting Goods, one of the largest firearms retailers in the United States, is moving further away from selling guns, even as the shift takes a toll on its earnings.

headline.main: Dick’s Sporting Goods Shifts From Guns Even as Sales Suffer
headline.print_headline: Dick’s Scales Back Guns Even as Sales Lag

docs.abstract: Once seen as a model of global cooperation, the Nissan-Renault alliance seethed with fear and rivalries, raising questions about its future.
docs.snippet: Once seen as a model of global cooperation, the Nissan-Renault alliance seethed with fear and rivalries, raising questions about its future.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — It was 2011, and Carlos Ghosn was preparing his automotive empire for its most ambitious phase yet. Under his plan, within five years, one of every 12 cars sold around the world would be made by Nissan of Japan. To achieve that goal and cut costs relentlessly, he said, Nissan would have to work closely with Renault, the French automaker he also controlled.

headline.main: Inside the Tensions at Carlos Ghosn’s Nissan
headline.print_headline: Fear, Division and an Imperious Boss: Nissan’s Spiral Into Turmoil

docs.abstract: Pursuit, a nonprofit jobs training program in Queens, is finding success at moving low-income New Yorkers into well-paying jobs.
docs.snippet: Pursuit, a nonprofit jobs training program in Queens, is finding success at moving low-income New Yorkers into well-paying jobs.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jukay Hsu is an enthusiastic Amazon backer. He wanted the company to build a big new campus in New York and participated in wooing it. He met with Amazon executives and appeared in a video pitch, and his tech-training program for disadvantaged New Yorkers was cited in the city’s written proposal to the company.

headline.main: Income Before: $18,000. After: $85,000. Does Tiny Nonprofit Hold a Key to the Middle Class?
headline.print_headline: A Way Out of Poverty and Into an $85,000 Tech Job

docs.abstract: At a recent industry gathering, retailers talked of how collecting customer data will help them compete in a landscape dominated by the internet.
docs.snippet: At a recent industry gathering, retailers talked of how collecting customer data will help them compete in a landscape dominated by the internet.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The chief executive of Saks Fifth Avenue’s parent company said stores would eventually recognize customers as soon as they walked in. FedEx showcased a robot that it thinks could ultimately make same-day deliveries on its own. The mall operator Macerich described the movable walls and fixtures that it was using to construct new stores for online-only brands.

headline.main: Stores See a Future Without ‘May I Help You?’ (They’ll Already Have Your Data)
headline.print_headline: Stores See a Future Where Your Data Guides Your Visit

docs.abstract: Top Chinese officials, looking at a skeptical audience both at home and abroad, pledge to open the country’s markets to foreign investment.
docs.snippet: Top Chinese officials, looking at a skeptical audience both at home and abroad, pledge to open the country’s markets to foreign investment.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Top Chinese economic policymakers promised this weekend that Beijing was ready to open up the country’s economy to more market-based competition and international trade, in the latest sign of strong Chinese interest in ending a multibillion-dollar trade war with the United States.

headline.main: China Pledges Openness in Hopes of Reaching a Trade Deal
headline.print_headline: Hoping for Deal With U.S., China Promises Openness

docs.abstract: A compilation of state data indicates a big decline for the electric-car maker after a federal tax credit was reduced.
docs.snippet: A compilation of state data indicates a big decline for the electric-car maker after a federal tax credit was reduced.
docs.lead_paragraph: For weeks, analysts have speculated that Tesla has seen a marked drop in sales since the beginning of the year, and the electric-car maker’s recent gyrations on price cuts and cost-saving initiatives have only bolstered their suspicions.

headline.main: Tesla Sales Slump as ’19 Starts Is Hinted At in State Data
